South Africa’s Corn Crop May Fall 14% to Lowest Since 2006/7

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-02-24T13:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/south-african-corn-crop-may-fall-14-to-the-lowest-level-since-2006-7.html
  South Africa  may produce the
smallest corn crop this year since the 2006/7 season, the
nation’s Crop Estimates Committee said.  The crop may decline 14 percent to 11.04 million metric
tons, from 12.82 million tons in the 2009/10, Marda Scheepers, a
spokeswoman for the committee, said by phone from  Pretoria 
today.  The white corn crop may fall 19 percent to 6.36 million
tons, she said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at   ajordan11@bloomberg.net  